						<!-- title of post -->
						  
							<h2 class="title">
								<a href="http://financeeasy.info/2012/04/20/how-superheroes-save/" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent Link to How superheroes save">How superheroes save</a>
							</h2>
												
						<!-- header-->
						<div class="meta meta-date">
							<span class="meta-info meta-text meta-link">Posted in <a href="http://financeeasy.info/category/personal-finance/" title="View all posts in Personal Finance" rel="category tag">Personal Finance</a></span>
						</div>	
						
						<!-- content  -->								
						<div class="entry">									
														<p>They don’t have a financial plan. Some of them can’t even claim a day job. But Marvel Comics, teaming up with Visa Canada, has produced a comic depicting superheroes teaching us to be super savers.</p>
<p>The Avengers comic “Saving the Day” will become available on Thursday as part of Superhero Week April 23-27. The aim is to introduce children to basic money concepts such as budgeting, saving and banking.</p>
<p>Visa Canada notes that its own studies show 31% of children 12-18 receive their information about how to manage their finances from school with the rest left to look to other resources.</p>
<p>The comic follows Spider-Man as he joins up with the Avengers to tackle Mole Man while managing to sneak in a few lessons on the banking system.</p>
<p>The <em>Financial Post</em> asked a comic book expert, a financial planner and a senior wealth management advisor to look at how these superheroes and villains rank in the financial literacy department. It turns out Spider-Man needs to think about caring for his elderly aunt, Iron Man needs to get serious about getting charitable and it might be time for Mole Man to put something away for a rainy day. <strong><em>— SCROLL OVER IMAGE BELOW TO READ MORE</em></strong></p>
<p><script type="text/javascript">__tlid = '177486396221554690';setTimeout(function(){(function(d,t){var s=d.createElement(t),x=d.getElementsByTagName(t)[0];s.type='text/javascript';s.async=true;s.src=('https:'==document.location.protocol?'https:':'http:')+'//www.thinglink.com/jse/embed.js';x.parentNode.insertBefore(s,x);})(document,'script');},0);</script><br />
<img class="alignnone" title="Saving the Day" src="http://ww3.nationalpost.com/thinglink/FP0421_webmarvel.gif" alt="" width="940" height="933" /></p>
<p>ILLUSTRATION BY STEVE MURRAY</p>
